name: mixed_jkp9ky
source:
def mixed_jkp9ky(x, y):
    t1 = 1 / (1 + jnp.exp(-x))
    t2 = jnp.power(jnp.abs(t1), jnp.abs(y) % 3 + 1)
    t3 = jnp.std(t2)
    return t3

    i:f32[4] = jit[

    u:f32[] = jit[

      jaxpr={ lambda ; t:f32[4] v:i32[]. let
          w:f32[] = jit[

                  shape=(1,)

                ] x
                z:f32[1] = div y 4.0:f32[]
                ba:f32[4] = sub t z
                bb:f32[4] = square ba
                bc:f32[] = convert_element_type[
                  new_dtype=float32
                  weak_type=False
                ] v
                bd:f32[] = sub 4.0:f32[] bc
                be:f32[] = reduce_sum[axes=(0,) out_sharding=None] bb
                bf:f32[] = div be bd
                bg:bool[] = gt bd 0.0:f32[]
                w:f32[] = jit[
                  name=_where
                  jaxpr={ lambda ; bg:bool[] bf:f32[] bh:f32[]. let
                      bi:f32[] = convert_element_type[
                        new_dtype=float32
                        weak_type=False
                      ] bh
                      w:f32[] = select_n bg bi bf
                    in (w,) }
                ] bg bf nan:f32[]
              in (w,) }
          ] t v
          u:f32[] = sqrt w
        in (u,) }
    ] t 0:i32[]
  in (u,) }
